<HEADLINE>
<P>
MORNING REPORT: MEET THE PRESS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ALEENE MacMINN, Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Thursday at noon at Culver City Studio, actress Diane Ladd of ABC's upcoming 
movie about Rock Hudson will turn over a check for $25,000 to the American 
Health Foundation to be used to treat persons with AIDS. Ladd and Hudson became 
friends when they starred in "Embryo" in 1976, and since his death she has 
worked to combat AIDS. The $25,000 represents half of her $50,000 one-week 
salary for "Rock," in which she plays Kay Fitzgerald, Hudson's mother. Thomas 
Ian Griffith plays Hudson in the film. ALEENE MacMINN 
