<HEADLINE>
<P>
MORNING REPORT: FIRST OFF . . . 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ALEENE MacMINN, Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KCET Channel 28 has quietly canceled its gala 25th anniversary party at the 
Hollywood Bowl on Sept. 28. A spokesman for Los Angeles' public TV station 
cited the "inability to get the name performers that we needed on that date." A 
public announcement was not made, the spokesman added, because "the show never 
officially went on sale." It was, however, promoted in the September issue of 
KCET Magazine featuring Rita Moreno, Robert Merrill and Big Bird. Tickets 
ranged from $75-$4. "A lot of performers we hoped to get were simply not 
available," the spokesman added. So the station cancelled "rather than invite 
people to a second-class show." ALEENE MacMINN 
</P>
</TEXT>
