<HEADLINE>
<P>
WOMAN CROSSING I-5 STRUCK, KILLED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A Mexican woman was killed early Tuesday when she was struck by a pickup truck 
as she attempted to cross the southbound lanes of Interstate 5, about 10 miles 
north of Oceanside, according to the California Highway Patrol. 
</P>
<P>
Rita Aguilar Torres, 36, died at the scene from multiple injuries, said deputy 
coroner Max Murphy. 
</P>
<P>
Torres was apparently trying to follow her two children across a stretch of the 
busy freeway, about 3 1/2 miles north of Las Pulgas Road, when she was hit at 
5:30 a.m. by a pickup driven by Kenneth Freistat, 50, of Long Beach, CHP 
officer Jerry Bohrer said. 
</P>
<P>
Bohrer said he didn't know the ages of the children or whether Torres was an 
illegal alien. 
</P>
<P>
Freistat was not cited. 
</P>
</TEXT>
