<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE NATION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Evangelist Jim Bakker suffered stress and not mental illness when he collapsed 
Thursday, his wife said. "After 2 1/2 years of sheer mental torture, he was 
just stressed out," Tammy Faye Bakker said in a taped statement telecast on the 
Jim and Tammy Show. Meanwhile, Bakker's lawyers filed a motion seeking a 
mistrial on grounds that the collapse of a witness during defense 
cross-examination last week in U.S. District Court in Charlotte, N.C., 
prejudiced the jury. The U.S. Marshal's Office said a hearing would be held 
today to determine if Bakker is competent to stand trial on fraud and 
conspiracy charges. 
</P>
