</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE STATE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Assemblyman Gary A. Condit (D-Ceres) will get a seat on the House Agriculture 
Committee if he wins a Sept. 12 special election for a vacant congressional 
seat, House Majority Leader Richard A. Gebhardt (D-Mo.) said in Fresno. San 
Joaquin Valley farm interests traditionally have had a seat on the powerful 
committee. Condit is running against several Republicans and a Libertarian for 
the seat vacated last May by Democrat Tony Coelho, who resigned when questions 
were raised about his ethics in business dealings. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Brief 
</P>
</TYPE>
