<HEADLINE>
<P>
CARRIER AMERICA GOING THROUGH SUEZ CANAL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
SUEZ, Egypt 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The aircraft carrier America and four accompanying warships entered the Suez 
Canal on Tuesday on their way from the Persian Gulf to join the U.S. 6th Fleet 
in the Mediterranean, a canal official said. 
</P>
<P>
The official identified the ships accompanying the America as the Mobile Bay, a 
guided missile cruiser; the Lawrence, a guided missile destroyer; the fast 
combat support ship Seattle, and the Joseph Hewes, a frigate. 
</P>
