<P>
ISRAELIS SLAY GUERRILLA IN SOUTHERN LEBANON 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From United Press International 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
JERUSALEM 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Israeli soldiers killed a guerrilla during a clash in Israel's self-declared 
security zone in southern Lebanon, the army said. 
</P>
<P>
Before dawn Tuesday, an Israeli patrol spotted three guerrillas south of the 
village of Ramiye in the center of the security zone, an army spokesman said. 
</P>
<P>
The patrol opened fire, killing one guerrilla, and two others escaped, the 
spokesman said. 
</P>
