<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN DIEGO SPORTS ET CETERA: SERVICES FOR DEYNA ON SATURDAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Services for former Socker Kaz Deyna, who died in an automobile accident 
Friday, will be Saturday at noon at the Carmelite Monastery, 5158 Hawley Blvd. 
in Normal Heights. 
</P>
<P>
The service will be conducted in Polish, Deyna's native tongue, and English. It 
will be open to the public. 
</P>
<P>
</P>
<P>
FOOTBALL 
</P>
<P>
Sophomore defensive ends Mark Hyatt (6-feet-4, 235 pounds) and Steve 
Matuszewicz (6-feet-4, 215) will not be red-shirted this season as planned, San 
Diego State football Coach Al Luginbill said. 
</P>
<P>
Luginbill was considering red-shirting the pair but said that because of lack 
of depth on defense, he could not afford to. 
</P>
