<HEADLINE>
<P>
SURGERY SIDELINES CHRIS PEERY; 
</P>
<P>
CANYON TAILBACK OUT INDEFINITELY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By VINCE KOWALICK, Times Staff Writer 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Canyon High tailback Chris Peery underwent emergency urological surgery Tuesday 
night and will miss at least the first month of the season, according to Coach 
Harry Welch. 
</P>
<P>
Peery (6-foot-1, 210 pounds), who rushed for 1,418 yards and 22 touchdowns as a 
junior last season, was recovering at Valley Presbyterian Hospital on Tuesday 
evening after undergoing surgery for a non-football injury in the groin area, a 
hospital spokeswoman said. Peery was hospitalized Tuesday afternoon after 
complaining of pain since early Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
"He woke up at three in the morning in intense pain," Welch said. "He rested 
all day Saturday. He came to school today to register and was worse." 
</P>
<P>
Welch said that Peery will be lost for "a minimum of a month," possibly the 
entire season. "I don't know," he said. "Obviously, we're in shock." 
</P>
</TEXT>
