<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Sara Lee to Drop 'Light' Claim: Sara Lee Corp. will drop the words "light 
classics" from the packages and advertising of some whipped dessert products 
under an agreement it signed with the attorneys general of nine states. 
Although the company said the complaint has no merit, it said it settled the 
suit to save legal expenses and will pay $80,000 for the costs of the 
government investigation. A Sara Lee spokesman said the attorneys general 
objected on the grounds that light implied fewer calories. The nine states 
involved are California, Iowa, Illinois, Massachusetts, Minnesota, Missouri, 
New York, Texas and Wisconsin. 
</P>
</TEXT>
