<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
T-Bill Rates Fall: The Treasury Department sold $7.2 billion of new three-month 
bills at an average discount rate of 7.88%, down from 7.94% last week. Another 
$7.2 billion of new six-month bills was sold at an average discount rate of 
7.87%, down from 7.88% last week. The new discount rates understate the actual 
return to investors -- 8.15% for three-month bills, with a $10,000 bill selling 
for $9,800.80, and 8.31% for a six-month bill selling for $9,602.10. The 
discount rate reflects the price discount received when government securities 
are purchased at less than face value. 
</P>
</TEXT>
