30 E. GERMANS RISK DASH TO WEST 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
BUDAPEST, Hungary 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
At least 30 East Germans tired of awaiting permission for a mass exodus to the 
West made a risky overnight dash across the Hungarian border into Austria, the 
Red Cross said today. 
</P>
<P>
In Bonn, West German officials acknowledged they were making little progress in 
changing the minds of Communist East German leaders who intervened with 
Hungarian authorities to block the departure of about 5,500 refugees. As many 
as 20,000 are said to be waiting to leave. 
</P>
<P>
East German officials on Tuesday set up camp outside a tent community in 
Budapest sheltering many of the would-be emigres and began trying to persuade 
them to return to East Germany, only to meet with derision. 
</P>
